The paper deals with the classification of radiology reports using machine learning models, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance metrics of the models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves identifying frequent tokens in the reports, which is related to information retrieval, falling under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
